3:02 PM Prosecuting attorney Jack A. Pitzo in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Lavontae M Williams in court.  Attorney Cassandra A Miller Ms. in court for Lavontae M Williams. 
Case called for plea and sentencing.
Court conducts plea colloquy.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 is dismissed and read in.
Recommendations by the State.  Recommendations by the Defense.  Statement by defendant.

The Court Orders the Following:

Count 1:
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
90 Days Huber with RELEASE FOR WORK, WORK SEARCH, EDUCATION AND TREATMENT.  (Credit - 52 days if revoked).  CONSECUTIVE to any current sentence

Term of Probation: 1 Year CONCURRENT with any current probation
Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No contact with Sahara Trading Post, Designer Shoe Warehouse, Victim A or Victim B.
-	Mental Health evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Follow through with current mental health treatment and medications;
-	Absolute Sobriety; 
-	Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	All prescriptions to be filled at the same pharmacy
-	Inform agent of all prescriptions;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctor's prescription;
-	Work to Obtain a valid Driver's License within the first 19 months of probation;
-	No new law violations;

COSTS:  $ 243.00

DNA Surcharge: $ 200.00

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.  As an alternative to payment the defendant may complete community service as approved by the Agent.  Each hour of community service to equal $25.00 towards financial obligations.
